<font color="#FF0000">POLITICAL REFUGEES</font><br>
<tt>Mon May 26  5:08:07 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
i undestand what the topic is about,or what the beef is?<br>
if you talk the talk and walk the walk,you produce.<br>
after many years of bitter anger with the gooks,we dicided to<br>
do something with our anger and end the war with the gooks<br>
started talking to the refuguees and political prisoners from<br>
southeast asia,boy!did a learned a lot,my enemy was a brother<br>
i found that they were vietnam veterans,had ptsd,had lost close friends<br>
they were not welcome to america,homeless,and have deep regrets about the war<br>
sounds familiar?if somebody understands us is the vietnamese<br>
our destiny is tied together,I'M a member of a allianze of vietnam vets and vietnamise political prisoners<br>
our vietnamize counterparts were staff officers,embassy translators,usaid,members of goverment.<br>
after we left vietnam,they were left behind,they were taken as political prisoners and put in prision,<br>
some up to 15 yrs,they are now in our country as refugees,on welfare,with tons of social problems<br>
unwanted and ignored,we dont even do this to our enemys!,we are going to vietnan<br>
in d<br>
roves,as tourist,to see the old sites,to remember and enbracing our old enemys as close friends.<br>
but god forgive our allies,we speak respectfully of the nva,because they were brave.<br>
the gooks were the farmers and the lazy arvns,that the way we saw them,but the people i meet now have<br>
a story thats different,i see them with different eyes now,Im older now more wise more compasionate,and more tolerante<br>
of diversity,I:m not sure anymore of rigth or wrong but i know that that friends that i lost in vietnam would like me to<br>
seek the thruth and do the rigth thing,so this my little story,welcome home boys.
